textDisplay: No one could have ever imagined an anime with 12 endings for 12 episodes... It just sounds insane, all the effort that they must have done... Just straight up bananasEDIT: Thank you all for sharing other anime with a similar situation. I do feel that Chainsaw man still stands above them all because of the quality of the ending videos (they are really different from one another, take ending 3 for example), 12 different artists (and there are some big names among them). So those factors combined, makes it a really special case. But I stand corrected, it's not the first anime with a different ending for almost every episode.
textOriginal:
No one could have ever imagined an anime with 12 endings for 12 episodes... It just sounds insane, all the effort that they must have done... Just straight up bananas


EDIT: Thank you all for sharing other anime with a similar situation. I do feel that Chainsaw man still stands above them all because of the quality of the ending videos (they are really different from one another, take ending 3 for example), 12 different artists (and there are some big names among them). So those factors combined, makes it a really special case. But I stand corrected, it's not the first anime with a different ending for almost every episode.

textDisplay: *Deon's Chainsaw Journey Day #12:* It's official... After discovering the first opening of this *Chainsaw Man* 12 days ago to this date...BEST ANIME OPENING ALL OF 2022 AND MY MOST-FAVORITE CHAINSAW MAN ENDING TO DATE!* ☯Seriously, I've listened to this on repeat for 13 TIMES when I was walking to Dollar Tree to buy myself Meat Lasagna for dinner tomorrow that cost me $1.25 since I have no more money left 'til my mother comes by in the morning to give me more to buy groceries for keeping our house clean when it comes to cleaning the microwave & fridge and just CAN'T STOP! 🛑Well, I stopped listening as I was walking back home to save my energy as I was getting an adrenaline rush and sweating a bit like a wet dog before arriving back home upstairs lol but HOW ON MT. FUJI is this soundtrack SO GOOD?! With the heavy metal theme in the beginning which really frightened me as I'm not a fan of dark music as it gives me some triggers and hurts my autistic ears but starting @ 0:52 is when I couldn't stop rewinding it 101%! I just am lost for words as I even started to have Togepi's Fake Tears in public seeing Pochita being inside Denji's heart @ 1:16 as Pochita reminds me of my Siberian Husky (Elijah) that was there for me before my mother's boyfriend & I had to put him down due to abdomen cancer and still tearing up a tad like a lonely lost kitten as I was typing this comment down while my Chicken Terriyaki Noodles cool off inside the microwave. 😿*DŌMOARIGATŌ MAPPA!* 📿*I MISS YOU SO MUCH ELIJAH AS I HOPE YOU'VE BEEN REINCARNATED INTO STRONGER HUSKY AND BEING TAKEN CARE OF BY A NEW KINDHEARTED OWNER OUT THERE AFTER YOU'VE BEEN ADOPTED!*🐕‍🦺*PS:* I MISS YOU TOO POCHITA BEING THE BEST ANIME & MOST ADORABLE DOG IN EXISTENCE! 🐶*PSS EDIT:* I just noticed that it's Trending #26 right now as it used to be #31 when I was walking back home from the store earlier! 😁*-愛、デオン* ♠2022 年 10 月 26 日 / October 26. 2022 @ 10:01pm. 🗾*Maximum Hormone ADDED to my Chainsaw Man nightly soundtrack playlist!* 🎧🎶🌚
textOriginal:
*Deon's Chainsaw Journey Day #12:* It's official... After discovering the first opening of this *Chainsaw Man* 12 days ago to this date...

BEST ANIME OPENING ALL OF 2022 AND MY MOST-FAVORITE CHAINSAW MAN ENDING TO DATE!* ☯

Seriously, I've listened to this on repeat for 13 TIMES when I was walking to Dollar Tree to buy myself Meat Lasagna for dinner tomorrow that cost me $1.25 since I have no more money left 'til my mother comes by in the morning to give me more to buy groceries for keeping our house clean when it comes to cleaning the microwave & fridge and just CAN'T STOP! 🛑

Well, I stopped listening as I was walking back home to save my energy as I was getting an adrenaline rush and sweating a bit like a wet dog before arriving back home upstairs lol but HOW ON MT. FUJI is this soundtrack SO GOOD?! 

With the heavy metal theme in the beginning which really frightened me as I'm not a fan of dark music as it gives me some triggers and hurts my autistic ears but starting @ 0:52 is when I couldn't stop rewinding it 101%! 

I just am lost for words as I even started to have Togepi's Fake Tears in public seeing Pochita being inside Denji's heart @ 1:16 as Pochita reminds me of my Siberian Husky (Elijah) that was there for me before my mother's boyfriend & I had to put him down due to abdomen cancer and still tearing up a tad like a lonely lost kitten as I was typing this comment down while my Chicken Terriyaki Noodles cool off inside the microwave. 😿

*DŌMOARIGATŌ MAPPA!* 📿

*I MISS YOU SO MUCH ELIJAH AS I HOPE YOU'VE BEEN REINCARNATED INTO STRONGER HUSKY AND BEING TAKEN CARE OF BY A NEW KINDHEARTED OWNER OUT THERE AFTER YOU'VE BEEN ADOPTED!*🐕‍🦺

*PS:* I MISS YOU TOO POCHITA BEING THE BEST ANIME & MOST ADORABLE DOG IN EXISTENCE! 🐶

*PSS EDIT:* I just noticed that it's Trending #26 right now as it used to be #31 when I was walking back home from the store earlier! 😁

*-愛、デオン* ♠

textDisplay: マキシマム ザ ホルモンを名前しか知らなかった素人なんだけど、挿入歌とedに携わるってなって皆反応良くてどんなもんかな～と思ったら、めちゃくちゃチェンソーマンに合ってるし曲の構成スゴいな…………。無限に聞いちゃう。永久機関が完成しちまったなアア～！！追記:気づいたら沢山反応あってビックリしてる。ミクスチャーロックというか、ロック自体あまり聴かないからとても参考になる。ありがとう腹ペコたち‼️知人に腹ペコがいた気がするのでいろいろ聞きます

textDisplay: Chainsaw Man's third ending (2022 -) is the craziest and most psychedelic (so far). Because if there is a band that knows how to capture the essence of both Heavy Metal and Chainsaw Man in such an insanely appropriate and consistent way, it is Maximum the Hormone. Also, I love the portrayal of Makima as The Virgin Mary, it's so cool, as it completely symbolizes Denji's vision, and I love that.
textOriginal: Chainsaw Man's third ending (2022 -) is the craziest and most psychedelic (so far). Because if there is a band that knows how to capture the essence of both Heavy Metal and Chainsaw Man in such an insanely appropriate and consistent way, it is Maximum the Hormone. Also, I love the portrayal of Makima as The Virgin Mary, it's so cool, as it completely symbolizes Denji's vision, and I love that.

textDisplay: Man Likely a Victim of Forced Organ harvestingYu Han told the story of her father.Yu Han, who currently lives in the United States, talked about what happened to her father. Mr. Han Junqing was a resident in Fangshan District, Beijing. He used to suffer heart disease and high blood pressure with both legs infested with pus all year long. Not long after starting to practice Falun Gong, his health improved dramatically. In addition, his bad habits such as smoking, alcoholism, and bad temper were gone.Mr. Han was arrested in March 2004 and held at the Fangshan Detention Center, where he was badly beaten by over ten officers. He died less than three months later and his body was cremated immediately.“I saw his body before he was cremated. He was terribly thin and bruised all over, but from his throat there was an incision all the way down to his torso,” his daughter recalled, “In his stomach area, we could feel a hard block of ice beneath the skin that was stitched with thick black thread.”The police said he died of heart attack, but Yu Han knew it was not true since her father had been healthy all along. “It wasn’t until three years later that I learned the truth – tens of thousands of prisoners of conscience like my father had been killed for their organs. That night I cried for hours until I passed out...” she added. That is why she hoped the atrocity could be stopped so that other families would not have to suffer miserably like her.
textOriginal:
Man Likely a Victim of Forced Organ harvesting

Yu Han told the story of her father.

Yu Han, who currently lives in the United States, talked about what happened to her father. Mr. Han Junqing was a resident in Fangshan District, Beijing. He used to suffer heart disease and high blood pressure with both legs infested with pus all year long. Not long after starting to practice Falun Gong, his health improved dramatically. In addition, his bad habits such as smoking, alcoholism, and bad temper were gone.

Mr. Han was arrested in March 2004 and held at the Fangshan Detention Center, where he was badly beaten by over ten officers. He died less than three months later and his body was cremated immediately.

“I saw his body before he was cremated. He was terribly thin and bruised all over, but from his throat there was an incision all the way down to his torso,” his daughter recalled, “In his stomach area, we could feel a hard block of ice beneath the skin that was stitched with thick black thread.”

The police said he died of heart attack, but Yu Han knew it was not true since her father had been healthy all along. “It wasn’t until three years later that I learned the truth – tens of thousands of prisoners of conscience like my father had been killed for their organs. That night I cried for hours until I passed out...” she added. That is why she hoped the atrocity could be stopped so that other families would not have to suffer miserably like her.
